# Auth implementation conventions

- Keep request authentication in `authn` clients/services; do not duplicate credential parsing in API handlers.
- For new auth mechanisms, implement `authn.Client` (and `ContextAwareClient` when request-driven), with clear `Test()` and stable `Priority()`.
- Register auth clients and sync hooks in `pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/registration.go`; avoid ad hoc wiring in unrelated packages.
- Return and propagate `authn.Identity` with correct `ClientParams` (`SyncUser`, `FetchSyncedUser`, `SyncPermissions`, org/team sync flags) instead of custom side effects.
- Use `authn.Service.Login()` to create sessions; write/remove cookies via `authn.WriteSessionCookie()` and `authn.DeleteSessionCookie()`.
- Keep session/token lifecycle in `auth.UserTokenService` (`authimpl`): store hashed tokens only, use rotation/revocation APIs, and preserve max lifetime + inactive lifetime behavior.
- For OAuth/SAML flows, validate redirect/state/PKCE via existing authn/api helpers; never introduce open redirects (always validate redirect targets).
- Set auth context through `contexthandler` middleware and consume `ReqContext`/requester identity downstream; do not bypass context population.
- Enforce authorization through access-control evaluators (`ac.EvalPermission`, `ac.EvalAny`, `AuthorizeInOrgMiddleware`) rather than manual role checks.
- Preserve existing error semantics (`Unauthorized` vs `Forbidden` vs `NotFound`) and public error messages for login/auth endpoints.

Primary references:
- `pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/service.go`
- `pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/registration.go`
- `pkg/services/auth/authimpl/auth_token.go`
- `pkg/services/contexthandler/contexthandler.go`
- `pkg/services/accesscontrol/middleware.go`
- `pkg/api/login.go`
